title: Slow Cooker Chicken Tortilla Soup
directions: Stir Picante sauce, soup, cumin, garlic, pepper, chicken, corn, beans, and water in the crock pot.
Cover and cook on LOW for 4-5 hours... Make sure chicken is cooked all the way through.
Afterward, stir in tortilla strips, cheese, and cilantro and cook for 15 more minutes.
Serve with additional cheese and sour cream if desired.
ingredients: 2 cans Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup [1 10 1/2 oz. can and 1 large can]
1 lb skinless, boneless chicken breasts, cubed [roughly 4 breasts]
